ThisisanextensionofPCM.Whentheanaloguesignalissampled,
thedifferencefromtheprevioussignaliscalculated.Onlythe
differenceneedstobetransmitted.Providedthesignalchanges
relativelyslowlycomparedtothesamplingrate,thisdifference
willbeonaveragebesmallerthanthemaximumamplitudeofthe
signal,andthismethodwillrequirelessinformationtorepresent
thesamesignal.

àMultiplexingÄ

Whentransmittingsignalsoverlongdistances,suchasphone
lines,thecostofthecablescanbeveryhigh.Ifonewirewas
usedperphonecall,averylargenumberofcableswouldbe
required.Bymultiplexing,asinglelinecansupportmany
simultaneoussignals.Therearetwocommonwaysofachievingthis:

àFrequencyDivisionMultiplexing(FDM)Ä

Eachmessagesignalisusedtomodulateacarrieratadifferent
frequency.Allthemodulatedsignalsmaythenbeaddedtogether
andtransmitteddowntheline.Thereceivermustdemodulatethem
allindividually.

àTimeDivisionMultiplexing(TDM)Ä

Eachmessagesignalneedstobecompressedintime,andasmall
burstofsignalfromeachistransmittedinturn.Inpractice,
thisisusuallydonedigitally(bypulsecodemodulation:PCM).

